  "prompt": "Is there any chance to change from chennai campus to vellore campus after first year?",
  "response": "Yes, some universities and colleges do allow campus transfers after the first year, but this generally depends on the institution's policies, availability of seats, academic performance, and sometimes the reasons for the transfer request. If you are looking to transfer from Chennai campus to Vellore campus in a specific university like VIT (Vellore Institute of Technology), it is best to directly inquire with the administration office or the academic affairs department for their transfer policies, application procedures, and eligibility criteria. Some institutions may require you to maintain a certain GPA, have no disciplinary actions against you, and submit a formal request or application for the transfer.\n\nMake sure to gather all necessary information and follow the formal procedures to increase the chances of a successful campus transfer.",
